modules.description: Converts between string and Cstruct.t representations within a Multihash_digestif.t structure. Works directly with string and Cstruct.t data types wrapped in the Multihash_digestif.t type. Useful when handling binary data in different formats, such as preparing hashes for network transmission or storage.

This module implements multihash encoding and decoding using the Digestif hashing library. It provides functions to create, parse, and manipulate multihash values from Cstruct.t buffers or strings, supporting operations like hashing, iteration, and pretty-printing. Concrete use cases include generating content identifiers for IPFS or other systems requiring self-describing hashes, validating multihash encodings from external data sources, and converting between string and buffer representations for network transmission or storage.
